This is Boost v1.67
Download from: https://www.boost.org/users/history/version_1_67_0.html

Boost is built with the following libraries
- program options
- python
- regex
- system
- thread

# Python user configuration
The Python version (2.7) must be set in bootstrap and then used in ./b2
If a version of python different to 2.7 is to be used, the versions should be updated in the commands

To configure the Python version - create a custom configuration file
```sh
touch ~/user-config.jam
```

Add the following lines - configuring the local python2.7 locations if different from these
```
using python : 2.7 : /usr/bin/python2.7 : /usr/include/python2.7 : /usr/lib/python2.7 ;
```

For Python 3.8 use the following instead:
```
using python : 3.8 : /usr/bin/python3.8 : /usr/include/python3.8 : /usr/lib/python3.8 ;
```

# Patch Boost for Python 3.8
As noted in this Stackoverflow post: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/54991157/cant-compile-boost-python-1-65-1-with-msvc2015
Boost pre 1.67 cannot build with python 3.7+.

The following patch fixes the issue pre Boost 1.67
https://github.com/boostorg/python/commit/660487c43fde76f3e64f1cb2e644500da92fe582#diff-467cabb22a6c637452d730accca26d2e
The file to modify is: `libs/python/src/converter/builtin_converters.cpp`

Remove the user-config file when finished

# Linux (x86) build and configuration

```
export DST_DIR=${REDBACKBOTS_CHECKOUT_DIR}/Util/Buildchain/boost
./bootstrap.sh --prefix=${DST_DIR} --with-python-version=2.7
./b2 --prefix=${DST_DIR} install
```

Replace 2.7 with 3.8 for different python versions

# V6 build and configuration (on x86 machine)

```
mkdir -p ~/software/boost
export DST_DIR=/home/nao/software/boost
cd <dir>/boost_1_67_....
./bootstrap.sh --prefix=${DST_DIR}
```

This needs to be run for both link=shared and link=static to get both
shared and static libraries from boost
```
./b2 --prefix=${DST_DIR}\
     --with-program_options \
     --with-python python=3.8 \
     --with-regex \
     --with-system \
     --with-thread \
     link=shared \
     link=static \
     cflags="-march=silvermont -mtune=silvermont" \
     install
```     

Replace 2.7 with 3.8 for different python versions


# For reference - Boost library configuration list

Component configuration:

    - atomic                   : not building
    - chrono                   : not building
    - container                : not building
    - context                  : not building
    - coroutine                : not building
    - coroutine2               : not building
    - date_time                : not building
    - exception                : not building
    - filesystem               : not building
    - graph                    : not building
    - graph_parallel           : not building
    - iostreams                : not building
    - locale                   : not building
    - log                      : not building
    - math                     : not building
    - mpi                      : not building
    - program_options          : not building
    - python                   : not building
    - random                   : not building
    - regex                    : not building
    - serialization            : not building
    - signals                  : not building
    - system                   : not building
    - test                     : not building
    - thread                   : not building
    - timer                    : not building
    - wave                     : not building


